Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, core, and thinly slice @red bell pepper{1}(halved, cored, thinly sliced) into strips. Peel and dice @sweet potatoes{1}(peeled, diced into 1/2-inch pieces). Halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}(halved, peeled, thinly sliced); mince a few slices until you have 2 TBSP.

Toss bell pepper, sweet potato, and sliced onion on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp}, @fajita spice blend{1%tbsp}, a big pinch of @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> For 4 servings, divide veggies between 2 sheets; roast on top and middle racks.

  Heat a drizzle of oil in a large, preferably nonstick, #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @ground turkey{10%oz} to pan; season with salt and pepper. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

While veggies roast, dice @tomato{1}(diced into 1/4-inch pieces). Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%oz}(roughly chopped). Quarter @lime{1}(quartered). Mince @jalapeño{1}(minced, ribs and seeds removed for less heat).

In a #medium bowl{}, combine tomato, minced onion, cilantro, juice from half the lime, a pinch of salt and pepper, and as much jalapeño as you like.

In a #small bowl{}, whisk together @vegan chipotle mayonnaise{4%tbsp} and @guacamole{4%tbsp}. Whisk in water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt.

Drizzle @flour tortillas{6} with @cooking oil{5%tsp}; brush or rub to coat both sides. Arrange on a second baking sheet in a single layer. Gently prick each tortilla in a few places with a #fork{}.

Bake on middle rack, flipping halfway through, until lightly golden, ~{4-5%minutes} per side.

> For 4, wait for veggies to finish roasting, then transfer veggies to a large bowl. Divide tortillas between baking sheets and bake on top and middle racks, flipping tortillas and swapping rack positions halfway through. TIP: Watch carefully—tortillas can quickly go from toasted to burned!

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat. Add @Old El Paso Refried Black Beans{1} and cook until warmed through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Divide tostadas between plates; spread each with refried beans. Top with roasted veggies, salsa, and creamy guacamole. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.

Top tostadas with beef or turkey along with roasted veggies.

> Ground Turkey is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.